<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
3.0-3.8 mm long (mean = 3.34 mm; n = 5); 2.92- 3.17
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the posterolateral extensions of elytra short, less than the width of apical emargination and declivity shallowly excavated; and declivity impunctate except for a single row of punctures running from the upper margin to the inner margin of the second declivital spine and thence to the apical emargination.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. emarginatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="emarginatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. emarginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is distinguished by the punctation of the declivity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
