</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="host">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Host plants.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Polyphagous, possibly with a preference for 
<taxonomicName family="Dipterocarpaceae" genus="D." lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Dipterocarpaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3875.1.1" author="Beaver, RA" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 82" refId="B26" refString="Beaver, RA, Sittichaya, W, Liu, L-Y, 2014. A synopsis of the scolytine ambrosia beetles of Thailand (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae). Zootaxa 3875: 1 - 82, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3875.1.1" title="A synopsis of the scolytine ambrosia beetles of Thailand (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3875.1.1" volume="3875" year="2014">Beaver et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.56.520" author="Hulcr, J" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="105 - 119" refId="B200" refString="Hulcr, J, 2010. Taxonomic changes in palaeotropical Xyleborini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae). ZooKeys 56: 105 - 119, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.56.520" title="Taxonomic changes in palaeotropical Xyleborini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae: Scolytinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.56.520" volume="56" year="2010">Hulcr (2010)</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. shoreae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="shoreae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. shoreae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. quadrispinus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="quadrispinus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. quadrispinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. fallax" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="fallax">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. fallax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) based on an illustration by 
<bibRefCitation author="Maiti, PK" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Survey of India, Kolkata" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B253" refString="Maiti, PK, Saha, N, 2004. Fauna of India and the Adjacent Countries. Scolytidae: Coleoptera (Bark- and Ambrosia-beetles) (Vol. 1). Part-1. Introduction and Tribe Xyleborini. Zoological Survey of India, Kolkata" title="Fauna of India and the Adjacent Countries. Scolytidae: Coleoptera (Bark- and Ambrosia-beetles) (Vol. 1). Part- 1. Introduction and Tribe Xyleborini." year="2004">Maiti and Saha (2004)</bibRefCitation>
as examination of type specimens was not possible. Maiti and Saha described the species as very morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. quadrispinus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="quadrispinus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. quadrispinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. fallax" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="fallax">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. fallax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The illustration clearly shows the diagnostic declivital puncturation and other features as described above which are distinct from 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. quadrispinus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="quadrispinus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. quadrispinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Two specimens of 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. shoreae" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="shoreae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. shoreae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected from the type locality determined by C.F.C. Beeson (MSUC) were also examined and are clearly distinct from those of 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. quadrispinus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="quadrispinus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. quadrispinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
